  "market_context": "Hourly chart of S&P 500 futures where price engaged the previous week's low (PWL), swept it with aggressive full-bodied candles, closed above a prior high to confirm a market structure shift, then retested a discount-order block and continued higher through the week.",
  "key_observation": "Price swept the previous week low with displacement candles, confirmed a market structure shift by closing above a prior swing high, then found support at a discount order block before continuing upward.",
  "analysis_steps": [
    "Step 1: Analyst identified the previous week low (PWL) as a key higher-time-frame liquidity level on the hourly chart.",
    "Step 2: Observed an aggressive move into PWL with full-bodied candles that touched and swept below the PWL level (liquidity sweep).",
    "Step 3: Confirmed market structure shift when price closed above a prior swing high following the sweep, establishing bullish structure.",
    "Step 4: Identified a bearish order block in the discount zone as a point of interest for a long setup after the MSS.",
    "Step 5: Watched price retest the order block, react, and then displace higher—validating the setup and continuation."
  ],
  "outcome": "Price continued higher throughout the week after the retest and displacement from the order block.",
  "lessons": "A valid market structure shift requires both a liquidity sweep and a close beyond structure; entries are highest probability when taken at POIs (e.g., order blocks) in the discount zone after MSS confirmation.",
